x4freetext: Range-energy data
Stacks consisted of Au Foils 20 micro-meter thick and
Cu absorber between them with thicknesses of 100 to
800 micro-meter. Al foils 100 micro-meter thick were
also inserted at particular places in the stack to
induce the monitor reaction. In order to determine the
absolute cross sections two identical au foils 4 micro-
thick were irradiated. The first was seprately
irradiated with deuteron beam, total charge being
measured in a faraday cup. The second was placed in
front of the stack irradiated under identical
conditions. The total charge in the stack was
determined from comparison of activities in two foils
and also from monitor reaction.
Equilibrium statistical model and hybrid model
Absolute errors in cross sections generally amount to
12-15 % whereas the accuracy within one excitation
function is of the order of 8-10%. For the most
unfavourable cases with small cross sections, small
gamma-ray abundances etc. The errors are about 20%.
Calculated incident energy within the stack are
estimated to be correct to +-1 MeV.
